office of the university registrar post office boxes student affairs office of the university registrar students faculty staff everyone resources and help stanford university student affairs all stanford search submit post office boxes post office boxes registrar's office information stanford universal students perennial personal information po boxes po box assistance contact location student services center tresidder union 2nd floor hours 9 00 am to 5 00 pm monday friday renting a po box if you currently have a po box assignment and will be an active student effective september 1 2011 your po box will be automatically renewed for the upcoming year no action on your part is required if you do not currently have a po box assigned to you new po boxes will be available for assignment on or after september 15 2011 if you would like to request your po box prior to september 15 use this pre categorized helpsu link you may then pick up your po box key at the student services center on or after september 15 2011 after september 15 you should visit the student services center in person to complete the po box assignment process the non refundable po box rental fee is $67 for a one year rental beginning on september 1 and ending on august 31 per quarter or partial year rentals are not available you must be a registered student within the academic year to acquire a stanford university po box note to undergraduates every undergraduate student is required to maintain a po box on campus to receive mail unless you live in one of the 36 row houses you will not be able to receive mail at your student residence if you do not live in a row house or maintain a po box you will be unable to receive mail on campus freshmen and transfer students are automatically assigned a po box all other students must apply for a box via the student services center tresidder union 2nd floor all post office boxes will be automatically renewed at the beginning of each academic year for registered students using the po box the us post office sorts the mail into the po boxes access to po boxes is 24 hours a day seven days a week us mail parcels and us express mail may be sent to the box a card or a key will be put into the box to notify the recipient that a package is waiting for pick up fed ex and ups will not deliver to a po box please direct all fedex and ups packages to student name 531 lasuen mall student po box number stanford ca 94309 terms and conditions of po box rental the terms and conditions for rental of a stanford university po box are as follows if you are leaving stanford for the summer please submit a temporary change of address you can submit a change of address with the stanford branch post office at least three weeks before you leave this service is free but it takes up to three weeks to process change of address cards are available in the lobby of all us post offices do not forget to enter a stop date a permanent change of address will remove your po box permanently and your po box will be assigned to another student po boxes may not be shared only mail addressed to you or members of your family with the same last name will be delivered no mail in care of c o your name will be accepted your box cannot be used to accept mail for a club group function consulting group business or events of any kind it also cannot be used to accept surveys voting ballots or fundraiser responses po boxes must be used in compliance with usps and university policies any deviations from the rules described above will cause your mail to be returned to sender or could result in a termination of your po box groups office of the university registrar printer friendly version calendar search the registrar's site search student affairs the student affairs division is responsible for programs and services that focus on students and their stanford experience while also engaging with faculty staff parents alumni and the community at large help resources forms publications academic 